title: Ubuntu Docker Image - ERROR: No matching distribution found for intel-openmp (from deeplabcut)
body:
I looked through the issues and noticed this was flagged for mac OS, but I'm having issues on Linux?

The docker image runs into issues on the "pip3 install deeplabcut" command in the docker file. See below. Everything up to this step (11/14) works fine and my network connection does not appear to be the issue. I've attempted resetting docker, this also has not worked. 

I do get the cautionary line "debconf: delaying package configuration, since apt-utils is not installed"
during step 8/14: RUN apt-get -y install ffmpeg

But this seems to be a notice with little significance.
